{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/copy-modified-files-git","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"e17520d9-f731-5839-b7d8-823f8d3a9d16","html":"<p>For one reason or another, I occasionally find myself in a place where I want to copy off all my modified files in my local git repository and start over.  This is usually due to painful merges where I just want a fresh start.  This is the one-liner you can use to do just that: </p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">git status --porcelain=v1 | awk {&#39;print $2&#39;} | xargs -I {} cp -r {} ../dir_with_changed_files</code></p>\n<p>Letâ€™s break down each part of this line in detail.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">git status --porcelain=v1</code></p>\n<p>You may be familiar with <code class=\"language-text\">git status</code>, adding the <code class=\"language-text\">--porcelain=v1</code> flag just changes the output from this:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 920px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/a1900/git_status.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24.130434782608695%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/01472/git_status.webp 240w,\n/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/222bd/git_status.webp 480w,\n/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/96051/git_status.webp 920w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 920px) 100vw, 920px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/0783d/git_status.png 240w,\n/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/782f4/git_status.png 480w,\n/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/a1900/git_status.png 920w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 920px) 100vw, 920px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/612c269b25ad2e75cd50e7bc74077243/a1900/git_status.png\"\n          alt=\"git status image\"\n          title=\"git status image\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>to this:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 549px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/1e4d8/git_status_porcelain.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 10.200364298724955%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAACCAYAAABYBvyLAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAaUlEQVQI1zWMwQqDQBBDNzOZ3UtFKmqpInjpof//gem6aw8hjwdJivGhvLrKFsoLFROVn9RYXDCIs4lvax2ni6sJgOLw7rfq98ovkw1QYj3xyVQ+VPlSXKyPEtoQRDtuudhvHzf/Y93/AKcfKwshH0YMAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/01472/git_status_porcelain.webp 240w,\n/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/222bd/git_status_porcelain.webp 480w,\n/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/d132e/git_status_porcelain.webp 549w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 549px) 100vw, 549px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/0783d/git_status_porcelain.png 240w,\n/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/782f4/git_status_porcelain.png 480w,\n/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/1e4d8/git_status_porcelain.png 549w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 549px) 100vw, 549px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/80b81338feed46a0e5459a966d0d8219/1e4d8/git_status_porcelain.png\"\n          alt=\"git status porcelain image\"\n          title=\"git status porcelain image\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">awk {&#39;print $2&#39;}</code></p>\n<p>This awk command will print the 2nd column of <a href=\"https://linux.die.net/man/3/stdout\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">standard out</a> (i.e. what is printed on the screen).  In our case, this will print out the column with the file names from the previous <code class=\"language-text\">git status --porcelain=v1</code> command.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">xargs -I {} cp -r {} ../dir_with_changed_files</code>    </p>\n<p>This portion of the command utilizes the <a href=\"http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man1/xargs.1.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">xargs</a> tool which allows iteration over things coming from standard input.  In this case, standard input for the <code class=\"language-text\">xargs</code> command is the standard output from the previous <code class=\"language-text\">awk</code> command.  Which take the list of files and copies it to the <code class=\"language-text\">../dir_with_changed_files</code> directory.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/copy-modified-files-git","tagSlugs":["/tag/command-line/","/tag/bash/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-05-15","description":"Copy off all your modified files and start over in git.","tags":["command line","bash"],"title":"Copy Your Modified Files in Git with 1 line","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/copy-modified-files-git"}}}